==English==

===Etymology===
Old French (compare French ''[[garde]]'') from Old Frankish *''wardo-'' (cognate with Old English [[weard]] > English [[ward]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/gɑ:d/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑː(r)d|-ɑː(r)d]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a person who [[protect]]s or [[watches]] [[over]] something
# a part of a [[machine]] which [[block]]s [[access]] to [[dangerous]] [[part]]s
# (''Aus'') [[panel]] of a [[car]] which [[enclose]]s the [[wheel]] [[area]], especially the front wheels.
# {{cattag|Basketball}} A [[relatively]] [[short]] [[player]], playing [[farther]] from the [[basket]] than a [[forward]] or [[center]].
# {{cricket}} The [[position]] on the [[popping crease]] where a [[batsman]] makes a [[mark]] to [[align]] [[himself]] with the [[wicket]] (see to [[take guard]])
# {{fb}} The offensive positions between the [[center]] and each of the [[offensive tackle]]s
# ''(sports)'' A player playing a position named guard

====Synonyms====
*[[fender]] (''US'', 3)
*[[wing]] (''British'', 3)

====Related terms====
*[[mudguard]]
*[[safeguard]]
*[[vanguard]]

